%description:

D3/D5(a) proving test, shape (ii): a signal-based PcapRecorder is added to
a host in a working UDP client/server simulation. PcapRecorder
(inet/common/packet/recorder/PcapRecorder.ned) is purely a signal listener
(subscribes to "transmissionEnded"/"receptionEnded" on the host's eth[*]
submodules by default) -- it never sits in the packet path, so adding it
must not change any application-visible behavior. StandardHost already
offers this as a plain parameter (recordPcap / numPcapRecorders, inherited
from LinkLayerNodeBase) -- no new NED is needed at all.

This file's ini has two configs:
- [Config Baseline]: *.server.recordPcap = false (default)
- [Config WithPcap]: *.server.recordPcap = true

Both configs were run manually and produce IDENTICAL app-level output
(client sends 6 UDP packets -- the 6th right at the sim-time-limit, never
delivered, in both configs alike -- server receives 5); this test commits
the WithPcap variant and additionally asserts the pcap file gets produced.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%extraargs: -c WithPcap
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = Test
ned-path = .;../../../../src
sim-time-limit = 5ms
cmdenv-express-mode = false

#omnetpp 5.0 - 5.1 compatibility:
eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

*.client.hasTcp = false
*.client.hasSctp = false
*.client.hasQuic = false
*.server.hasTcp = false
*.server.hasSctp = false
*.server.hasQuic = false

*.client.numApps = 1
*.client.app[0].typename = "UdpSourceApp"
*.client.app[0].source.packetLength = 100B
*.client.app[0].source.productionInterval = 1ms
*.client.app[0].io.destAddress = "server"
*.client.app[0].io.destPort = 1000

*.server.numApps = 1
*.server.app[0].typename = "UdpSinkApp"
*.server.app[0].io.localPort = 1000

# PcapRecorder needs a real (not just "declared correct") FCS to serialize frames
**.fcsMode = "computed"
**.checksumMode = "computed"

[Config Baseline]
*.server.recordPcap = false

[Config WithPcap]
*.server.recordPcap = true

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.node.inet.StandardHost;
import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv4.Ipv4NetworkConfigurator;

network Test
{
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv4NetworkConfigurator {
            @display("p=300,100");
        }
        client: StandardHost {
            @display("p=150,250");
        }
        server: StandardHost {
            @display("p=450,250");
        }
    connections:
        client.ethg++ <--> { datarate = 100Mbps; delay = 10us; } <--> server.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithPcap-0.sca
scalar Test.client.app[0].io "packets sent" 6
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: results/WithPcap-0.sca
scalar Test.server.app[0].io "packets received" 5
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: ls results/*Test.server*.pcap* 2>/dev/null | wc -l > pcapcount.out
%contains: pcapcount.out
1
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
